@startuml
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundcorner 14
skinparam DefaultFontName Arial
skinparam DefaultFontSize 14

skinparam class {
  BackgroundColor #F7F7F7
  BorderColor #222222
  FontColor #111111
}

skinparam ArrowColor #222222
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0

title Assurance artefact vocabulary (meta-model)\n(types + link semantics used for computed checks)

' Keep a clean top-down vocabulary view
top to bottom direction

class Hazard <<hazard>>
class RiskAssessment <<risk>>
class SILAllocation <<sil>>
class FSR <<fsr>>
class TSR <<tsr>>
class Architecture <<arch>>
class Verification <<verif>>
class Evidence <<evidence>>
class Confirmation <<confirm>>

RiskAssessment --> Hazard : **ADDRESSES**
SILAllocation --> RiskAssessment : **ALLOCATES**
FSR --> SILAllocation : **REFINES**
TSR --> FSR : **REFINES**
Architecture --> TSR : **REALIZES**
Verification --> FSR : **VERIFIES**
Evidence --> Verification : **EVIDENCES**
Confirmation --> Evidence : **REVIEWS**

legend left
  **Meta-model meaning**
  - Boxes = artefact *types* (Sphinx-Needs directives)
  - Edges = allowed *link types* (validated + used in graphs)
  - This vocabulary drives traceability views + lifecycle checks
endlegend

@enduml